                                            It isn't as intuitive as a user interface, but it is more powerful. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Think you know what's connected to your home network? You might be surprised. Learn how to check using <code>nmap</code> on Linux, which will let you explore all the devices connected to your network.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 14:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/423709/how-to-see-all-devices-on-your-network-with-nmap-on-linux/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why Some Websites Block VPNs (and How They Catch You)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-some-websites-block-vpns/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/52638820954_b8557161ae_o.jpg" length="302513" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[VPN]]></category><category><![CDATA[Privacy]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cybersecurity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            VPNs meet website roadblocks!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Using a <span class="display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id="209487"><a href="/738071/best-vpn-services/" target="_blank">VPN</a></span> protects your privacy and helps you bypass regional restrictions—but not all services allow it. If you’ve ever faced issues accessing a platform while connected to a VPN, the platform is probably blocking VPN traffic. So why do some websites block a VPN, and how exactly do they detect it?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 14:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-some-websites-block-vpns/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why Audiophiles Hate Soundbars (and Why They’re Wrong)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-audiophiles-hate-soundbars-and-why-theyre-wrong/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/looking-at-the-bose-smart-ultra-soundbar-from-the-left.jpg" length="397" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Speakers]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Soundbar]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't knock it till you try it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>An "audiophile" is someone who loves the experience of high-fidelity sound reproduction and appreciates a good soundstage and audio imaging. In fact, achieving higher levels of fidelity and more accurate sound reproduction is a goal that many audiophiles chase relentlessly—often at great cost.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 14:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-audiophiles-hate-soundbars-and-why-theyre-wrong/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[3 Cool Linux Apps Worth Trying This Weekend (October 10 - 12)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-apps-to-try-this-weekend-october-10/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-laptop-seen-from-the-front-running-linux-lite-with-two-other-distros-in-the-background.png" length="997" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Weekend]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Ready to browse the web from your Linux computer like it's 2008?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The weekend is the perfect time to put your Linux PC to the test and see what you can actually do with it. These are some native Linux applications I think are worth trying out if you haven't already installed them.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 13:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-apps-to-try-this-weekend-october-10/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Anker’s C2000 Gen 2 Wants to Power Your Fridge, RV, and More]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/anker-solix-c2000-gen2-wants-to-power-your-home-and-rv/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/c2000-gen-2-home-refrigerator.jpg" length="2022" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Portable Power Station]]></category><category><![CDATA[Anker]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This power station even supports dual-input fast charging. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Portable power banks are great for charging phones and tablets, but when you want to power a fridge, part of your home, or an RV, you'll want something a bit bigger. Anker's SOLIX line is a popular option, and the latest SOLIX C2000 Gen 2 is here to power everything.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 13:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/anker-solix-c2000-gen2-wants-to-power-your-home-and-rv/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Weekend Project: Personalize Your Raspberry Pi OS Command Line]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/weekend-project-personalize-your-raspberry-pi-os-command-line/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/img_0146.jpg" length="342" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Raspberry Pi]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY]]></category><category><![CDATA[Weekend]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Who knew customizing a terminal could be so fun?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Are you looking for a fun way to refresh your Raspberry Pi’s command line experience? You don’t have to look far to find a simple and fun way to overhaul the terminal on your Pi. With Oh My ZSH or Starship, you can have a fully customized Pi experience this weekend.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 11:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/weekend-project-personalize-your-raspberry-pi-os-command-line/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Ways to Access Your Home Assistant Server Remotely]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/access-your-home-assistant-server-remotely/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/home-assistant-green-on-an-entertainment-stand.jpg" length="1268" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home Assistant]]></category><category><![CDATA[VPN]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cybersecurity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Keep on eye on your place, wherever you are.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>It’s easy to recommend Home Assistant to anyone who wants a powerful and versatile smart home, but in its default state, the platform operates wholly offline. For many, this is a feature since it means there’s no reliance on the cloud.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 11:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/access-your-home-assistant-server-remotely/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This EcoFlow Station Is the Ultimate Power Outage Companion]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ecoflow-delta-3-max-plus-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/ecoflow-delta-3-max-plus-power-station-02.jpg" length="1288" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[EcoFlow DELTA 3 Max Plus]]></category><category><![CDATA[Portable Power Station]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Is your refrigerator running? Well, when you catch it, power it with this big battery.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>EcoFlow sells many portable power stations, but the <a href="https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/3607085/type/dlg/sid/UUhtgUeUpU2017125/https://us.ecoflow.com/products/delta-3-max-series-portable-power-station?variant=54718699962441&view=d3mp" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Delta 3 Max Plus</a> is one of the most versatile options. The 120V and 20A AC output support and rated capacity of 2048Wh makes it a great option for outdoors trips, home power outages, and everything in between. There are a few catches, though.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 10:01:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ecoflow-delta-3-max-plus-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[3 HBO Max Shows to Binge This Weekend (September 10 - 12)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hbo-max-shows-weekend-binge-october-10/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Derek Malcolm]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/hbo-max-logo-in-the-foreground-with-popcorn-a-clapperboard-and-3d-glasses-in-the-background.png" length="3939" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[HBO Max]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Weekend]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            HBO Max has some of the best TV shows in the world, just ripe for the weekend picking.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>What I love most about <a href="https://www.hbomax.com/shows" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">HBO Max</a> is that even though I've been watching its shows and movies for more than 25 years, when I start digging back into its library, I'm amazed to uncover things I've never heard of or had nearly forgotten about. Of course, it also continues to crank out excellent new shows, but the breadth of options it provides is still impressive.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 08:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hbo-max-shows-weekend-binge-october-10/</guid></item></channel>
